beer.beer_description: This double dry hopped special edition of Countach is inspired by the 1985 LP 5000 Quatrovalvole, which featured a larger engine and double the amount of valves per cylinder. It had the same exotic engineering, sharp angles and bravado- but with more juice under the hood. This Hazy Double IPA was hand assembled with the finest designer hop products available and unleashes an experience that borders on sensory overload. Mango, tangerine, peaches & cream, melon candy and lime aide all blur by. Its quiet, but edgy bitterness is precisely balanced by its supple mouthfeel. The latest in our Dad’s Dream Ridez series—doors up, shades on, flavor at full throttle.
beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy

beer.beer_style: IPA - Imperial / Double New England / Hazy

beer.beer_description: Exotic, sharply angled and engineered for maximum juice. This Hazy Double IPA was fermented with an expressive yeast strain and dry hopped heavily with Nelson Sauvin, Citra Cryo, HBC 586 & Galaxy. The resulting flavors and aromas of mango, pink guava, juicy nectarine and ripe pineapple inspire and surprise at every turn. A nuanced amount of highly refined bitterness and a sumptuously mouthfeel make for a deceptively potent quaff. Inspired by the alluring combination of form and function possessed by its namesake, a classic that looked fast even when it was sitting still.
